That you did not joyne with the ſtronger ſide, I meane in appearance: That you did not joyne ſtrength to ſtrength, and adde more fuell alſo, to make the flame the more fierce and raging: for this is the manner of men, To oppreſſe the oppreſſed; to add to the affliction, and, like Mice, as to runne out, vvhen the Houſe is on fire: So to judge of Gods workes before they bee ripe, I meane before the FIFT ACT, and that is againſt the Rule De operi • us Dei 〈◊〉 quintum actū
